On Monday, November 08, 2004, at 10:49AM, Chris M. <busbodger(-at-)earthlink.net> wrote:

>By pass that ground cable with a jumper cable from the battery to the engine or starter. The wire ends may be cleaned and still it could be bad... 

FYI.

If you've ever shrugged off the sight of a little corrosion on the battery terminals, think again. A little corrosion goes a long way towards preventing the starter from getting enough current:

http://hyperphysics.phy-astr.gsu.edu/hbase/electric/autbat.html#c1

